cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of deep learning in understanding biological brain computations. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the comparison between learning signals in brains and machines. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is relevant as the paper briefly discusses the contribution of DL in visual object recognition. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses the learning signals of both brains and machines. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the limitations of scaling up current DL algorithms to achieve human level Theory of Mind.
